definition: variant of 為|为[wei4], because of/for/to
variant of 為|为[wei2]/as (i.e. in the capacity of)/to take sth as/to act as/to serve as/to behave as/to become/to be/to do
as (in the capacity of)/to take sth as/to act as/to serve as/to behave as/to become/to be/to do/by (in the passive voice)

sentences.english: As a qualified electronics engineer, I am not surprised by such findings.
sentences.chinese: 作为一名认证电子工程师，此种发现对我不足为奇。

sentences.english: Little wonder, then, that card issuers feel shell-shocked.
sentences.chinese: 不足为奇，那时信用卡公司觉得倍受打击。

sentences.english: So, it should not be surprised to see an oversold relief bounce in the coming days.
sentences.chinese: 因此未来数日标普出现超跌反弹行情是不足为奇的。

sentences.english: It's not surprising they want to escape.
sentences.chinese: 它们渴望逃脱就不足为奇了。

sentences.english: Not surprisingly, DePaul has one of the most diverse student bodies in the U.S.
sentences.chinese: DePaul拥有全美最综合的学生也就不足为奇了。

sentences.english: Not surprisingly, the company invests very little in its pumped storage plants today.
sentences.chinese: 不足为奇的是，今天公司很少投资抽水蓄能电站。

sentences.english: No wonder that the migrants are increasingly restive.
sentences.chinese: 因此外来人员日益感到不安也就不足为奇了。

sentences.english: In Utah, discovering a band of polygamists hardly raises an eyebrow.
sentences.chinese: 在犹他州发现一伙重婚者不足为奇。

sentences.english: When it is when there is envy in the Lotto , who not surprising.
sentences.chinese: 当它时，是在乐透，谁也就不足为奇羡慕。

sentences.english: A set of amazing experiments reveals it was no surprise.
sentences.chinese: 一个惊人的实验表明它是一套不足为奇。

sentences.english: In this context, China's housing oversupply isn't surprising.
sentences.chinese: 这种情况下，中国的住宅供应过剩也就不足为奇了。

sentences.english: We should not be surprised there is no Socratic dialogue with Hippocrates.
sentences.chinese: 因此医学院没有苏格拉底式的对话也就不足为奇了。

sentences.english: Loss of habitat is, unsurprisingly, the main threat to the plants.
sentences.chinese: 生境丢失是这些植物的主要威胁，这不足为奇。

sentences.english: It’s probably no surprise that these hearty legumes are good for you.
sentences.chinese: 这些营养丰富的豆类对你有好处也许是不足为奇的。

sentences.english: So, it should not be surprising to see some profit taking efforts in the coming days.
sentences.chinese: 因此，未来几天出现一些获利回吐盘不足为奇。

sentences.english: It comes as no surprise that taxes are fiercely resisted by the tobacco industry.
sentences.chinese: 烟草业因此强烈抵制烟草税也就不足为奇。

definition: to keep one's calm in the face of the unexpected/not to wonder at strange sights
logical/only to be expected/rational and clearly structured (of text)
see 未可厚非[wei4 ke3 hou4 fei1]
there are plenty of such people
to seem/to appear/(in a negative or interrogative sentence) to be sure
